Package: subtypeHeterogeneity
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2017-09-12
Title: Tumor subclonality of expression-based cancer subtypes 
Author: Ludwig Geistlinger, Lucas Schiffer, Marcel Ramos, Levi Waldron
Maintainer: Ludwig Geistlinger <ludwig.geistlinger@sph.cuny.edu>
Depends: 
    R(>= 3.5.0), 
    GenomicRanges, 
    SummarizedExperiment
Imports: 
    AnnotationFilter,
    EnsDb.Hsapiens.v75,
    GenomicFeatures,
    GenomeInfoDb, 
    Gviz,
    IRanges, 
    RCurl, 
    RTCGAToolbox, 
    RaggedExperiment, 
    S4Vectors, 
    TCGAutils, 
    circlize,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2, 
    methods,
    plotly,
    reshape2 
Suggests: 
    BiocStyle, 
    knitr, 
    rmarkdown
Description: Testing of the hypothesis that expression-based cancer subtypes 
    tend not to be shared between intratumor clones, implying that they 
    differentiate late in tumorigenesis. This hypothesis will be tested first
    by identifying subtype-associated DNA alterations (copy number and somatic 
    mutations), then testing whether those alterations display greater intra-
    tumor heterogeneity than other alterations. 
